column5: Heading to the lower tomorrow morning. Have a lot of room in boat.
DAMN!!!!!!
What time you think you will be off the water?
Paul fishing weekday? You retired?  Safe trip dude.
What time you think you will be off the water? Haven't thought about it. Was thinking all day. 7 to 3
River is mint right now
I'm excited. this has been on my bucket list for a while.
Wish I could join you Paul!! Already plans for tomorrow, but looks like you have a passenger! Have fun.. stay SAFE !
I'm excited. this has been on my bucket list for a while.   What, fishing with Paul, or fishing bows and lakers  on the lower?  Have fun
What, fishing with Paul, or fishing bows and lakers  on the lower?   It's not just an adventure.
It's not just an adventure.   Im sure he will enjoy Paul. LMAO  Safe fishing fellas.
Please report back, I'm planning on doing this trip on friday.  Be safe and good luck!
Have fun!!! Would love to fish down there for skis!!!

Paul fishing weekday? You retired?  Safe trip dude. LOL, Paul had another week of holidays left so took this week off   But Wednesday is the day/night I spend with my mom so I'm not going.  Hope you boys do well, I'm all out of rainbows
Paul can't it wait till Sunday?!  We both know you're not gonna get squat without me in the boat..
Without Joey in the boat all you'll be doing is releasing shiners!  :)   Goodluck boys!  Wish I could have jumped on this.

We are licking our wounds.   lots of laughs were had,but we are both scratching our heads at the results.  Thanks again Paul for showing me the ropes on the lower i feel much more confident heading out in my boat now .
Are you sure you were fishing with the right Paul???????????    Oh well, you got out and had time on the water with one of the originals here.

ok, they were slight chuckles, and they were  mostly at ourselves and our inaability to catch the dummest most suiciadal fish in lake ont while trolling, that somehow morphs into an elitist genius fish once it enters the river.
Was anyone else hooking up?  Some days it's a spoon bite out there, sometimes a shiner bite, etc.  I wouldn't feel too bad.

we only saw a handfulll of fish landed all day and most were on the u.s. side...it was not a great day for most anglers out there today.   something was off.  viz was good, but paul said he temps were up from from sunday and 10 degrees warmer than this time last year so we blamed it on that.
Did you guys fish the bar or just the river??
Thanks for the company  at the dirty old bar Andrew. Had a great time. Next time you get to work the trolling motor.  Kattor,We fished the river.
